<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="381" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2668</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-16">16
                                    November, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Will you not be kind
                            enough to acknowledge through the proper channels this message of the
                            Grand Duchess of Luxemburg<note n="8" xml:id="d381fn8">Telegram of Nov.
                                11, 1918, to President Wilson, <ref target="#pg_436">p.
                                436</ref>.</note> and say that her request about the passage of
                            troops has been transmitted to the Supreme War Council at Versailles; at
                            the same time transmitting the message to the Supreme War Council?</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>